14
00:02:49.108 --> 00:02:51.892
I am devoted.

15
00:02:51.944 --> 00:02:53.393
Your servant.

16
00:02:53.445 --> 00:02:56.730
You have a destiny to claim.

17
00:02:56.782 --> 00:02:59.733
Tell me...

18
00:02:59.785 --> 00:03:01.618
heavenly one.

19
00:03:03.906 --> 00:03:06.907
Tell me what you will
have me do.

20
00:03:06.959 --> 00:03:11.578
It is time to lay down
the sword. Wilkin Brattle.

21
00:03:11.664 --> 00:03:14.164
Your savior needs you

22
00:03:14.249 --> 00:03:17.918
to live the life
of a different man.

23
00:03:18.003 --> 00:03:19.803
Yes.

24
00:03:19.888 --> 00:03:23.256
I will.

25
00:03:23.342 --> 00:03:25.175
I understand.

26
00:03:29.976 --> 00:03:31.961
I will.

27
00:04:42.858 --> 00:04:46.901
_

28
00:05:25.547 --> 00:05:26.997
The dream?

29
00:05:30.886 --> 00:05:33.253
You're my only dream.

30
00:05:38.593 --> 00:05:42.062
Will you ever
tell me what you see?

31
00:05:43.348 --> 00:05:46.232
I see only
my lovely Petra.

32
00:05:50.105 --> 00:05:51.821
Oh. please.

33
00:05:51.907 --> 00:05:54.574
How can you desire such a cow?

34
00:05:54.609 --> 00:05:57.444
Oh. but a beautiful cow it is.

35
00:06:01.667 --> 00:06:03.416
Oh. he kicks fierce

36
00:06:03.452 --> 00:06:05.869
as his father
this morning.

37
00:06:05.954 --> 00:06:07.787
How do you know it's a he?

38
00:06:07.873 --> 00:06:09.289
Annora insists

39
00:06:09.341 --> 00:06:12.008
your firstborn will be an heir.

40
00:06:12.094 --> 00:06:14.377
Ah. we're taking divine council

41
00:06:14.463 --> 00:06:16.379
from the Slavic witch now.
are we?

42
00:06:16.465 --> 00:06:18.798
She's a healer. not a witch.

43
00:06:18.884 --> 00:06:22.135
Her herbs help
my weakness and sleep.

44
00:06:22.220 --> 00:06:23.887
And the silent hooded one--
does he offer

45
00:06:23.972 --> 00:06:25.472
dirt scratch visions
of our son's fate?

46
00:06:25.524 --> 00:06:26.523
Yea.

47
00:06:26.608 --> 00:06:28.274
Insists he'll be as pious

48
00:06:28.310 --> 00:06:31.194
and mule-headed as his father.

49
00:06:31.279 --> 00:06:32.779
I'm not mule-headed.

50
00:06:32.814 --> 00:06:34.698
- I just devote to the thing at hand.
- Good.

51
00:06:34.783 --> 00:06:36.366
Get your breeches up

52
00:06:36.451 --> 00:06:38.151
and devote to filling
the barrels.

53
00:06:38.203 --> 00:06:40.120
We're near out of water.

54
00:06:40.155 --> 00:06:41.988
Think that would be a task
for a strong cow.

55
00:06:48.463 --> 00:06:49.662
Oh.

56
00:06:49.715 --> 00:06:51.331
Oh. no! Oh!

57
00:06:53.635 --> 00:06:54.467
Ooh!

58
00:07:05.097 --> 00:07:13.436
_

59
00:07:34.509 --> 00:07:36.760
I'm sure they're wasted seeds.

60
00:07:36.845 --> 00:07:38.711
Like the rest.

61
00:07:41.016 --> 00:07:44.884
God will bestow us with a child
in his time. Erik.

62
00:07:44.970 --> 00:07:47.887
Then let God waste his hours

63
00:07:47.939 --> 00:07:50.440
chasing a barren hole
with swollen meat.

64
00:08:10.162 --> 00:08:11.661
Come.

65
00:08:20.255 --> 00:08:21.554
Morning. Baroness.

66
00:08:23.725 --> 00:08:25.558
Morning.

67
00:08:50.836 --> 00:08:52.785
Should I draw a bath. milady?

68
00:08:52.838 --> 00:08:56.339
I need more than a bath.

69
00:08:56.424 --> 00:08:59.259
sweet Isabel.

70
00:09:05.267 --> 00:09:07.100
So much more.

71
00:09:17.879 --> 00:09:22.319
♪ born with a heart ♪

72
00:09:22.897 --> 00:09:28.240
♪ that could ache
more than beat ♪

73
00:09:30.292 --> 00:09:36.162
♪ the mind of a killer ♪

74
00:09:36.214 --> 00:09:39.999
♪ the soul of the meek ♪

75
00:09:42.554 --> 00:09:48.174
♪ flock with no shepherd ♪

76
00:09:48.226 --> 00:09:54.280
♪ is a vulnerable game ♪

77
00:09:54.349 --> 00:09:57.183
♪ I can live
without a hearth ♪

78
00:09:57.235 --> 00:10:00.520
♪ without love ♪

79
00:10:00.572 --> 00:10:04.574
♪ but I do need a name ♪

80
00:10:07.329 --> 00:10:09.913
♪ Father. do you burn ♪

81
00:10:09.998 --> 00:10:13.416
♪ if your hand is in fire? ♪

82
00:10:13.501 --> 00:10:16.502
♪ does your head
spin with rage ♪

83
00:10:16.571 --> 00:10:20.006
♪ when fooled by the liars? ♪

84
00:10:20.075 --> 00:10:25.612
♪ King of the kings ♪

85
00:10:25.680 --> 00:10:30.266
♪ do you feel any pain? ♪

86
00:10:31.853 --> 00:10:34.602
♪ do you feel any pain? ♪

87
00:10:35.032 --> 00:10:37.589
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

88
00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:04.384
It is time.

89
00:11:11.593 --> 00:11:14.093
Your pagan confidant
awaits you.

90
00:11:16.264 --> 00:11:18.264
As does your
fur-covered squire.

91
00:11:19.517 --> 00:11:20.683
I'm looking.

92
00:11:20.769 --> 00:11:21.851
Calm yourself.

93
00:11:21.936 --> 00:11:23.269
You're such an impatient ewe.

94
00:11:30.161 --> 00:11:31.611
I'll sheer you raw.

95
00:11:31.663 --> 00:11:33.329
throwing that in my face.

96
00:11:33.415 --> 00:11:35.198
It was but one time.

97
00:11:35.283 --> 00:11:36.582
Very dark.

98
00:11:36.618 --> 00:11:38.785
She had familiar wool.

99
00:11:39.884 --> 00:11:41.385
I am true.

100
00:11:41.486 --> 00:11:43.287
And you're one to talk.

101
00:11:43.388 --> 00:11:44.621
Yeah. I see you in the fields.

102
00:11:44.722 --> 00:11:45.956
Your tartish play.

103
00:11:46.058 --> 00:11:48.292
Catching a rub
on every buck and ram.

104
00:11:48.393 --> 00:11:50.928
Mutton troubles.
my friend?

105
00:11:51.029 --> 00:11:52.562
Good day. Wilk. Petra.

106
00:11:52.663 --> 00:11:54.230
She's a bit of crankypox.

107
00:11:54.331 --> 00:11:55.665
Eh...

108
00:11:55.766 --> 00:11:56.999
I know.

109
00:11:57.101 --> 00:11:59.269
Perhaps Miriam
needs a little rest.

110
00:11:59.370 --> 00:12:01.204
That's all she does is sleep.

111
00:12:01.305 --> 00:12:03.173
Sleep. eat and shit.

112
00:12:03.274 --> 00:12:04.474
That's because it's a sheep.

113
00:12:04.575 --> 00:12:06.976
Eh?

114
00:12:09.480 --> 00:12:10.880
Oh. wit.

115
00:12:10.981 --> 00:12:12.648
Yeah.

116
00:12:12.749 --> 00:12:14.817
And a beautiful one.

117
00:12:14.918 --> 00:12:15.851
Yeah. I'm sorry. honeypot.

118
00:12:15.953 --> 00:12:17.453
I know. My fault.

119
00:12:21.058 --> 00:12:23.859
Love spreads like
a sweet healing balm.

120
00:12:23.961 --> 00:12:24.961
Yea.

121
00:12:32.368 --> 00:12:34.669
How many troops
with the tax collector?

122
00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:37.339
Three knights of the
familia. five horsemen.

123
00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:38.907
All skilled.

124
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:41.176
These hooded thieves
will meet a fierce surprise.

125
00:12:42.979 --> 00:12:45.947
And if their hoods
hide the faces of rebels?

126
00:12:46.048 --> 00:12:48.550
They would ride in numbers
with their wolf.

127
00:12:48.651 --> 00:12:50.919
The Byth Encil
wouldn't just steal

128
00:12:51.020 --> 00:12:53.555
a mere piece of your bounty.
my lord.

129
00:12:53.656 --> 00:12:56.291
These attacks are an
assertion of condition.

130
00:12:56.392 --> 00:12:59.495
It's righteous peasants setting
their own rule of tribute.

131
00:13:06.602 --> 00:13:08.436
Then crush them. Milus.

132
00:13:08.537 --> 00:13:11.005
They ignite the rabble.

133
00:13:11.106 --> 00:13:13.107
If they steal
from us again.

134
00:13:13.208 --> 00:13:16.310
we'll have more aspiring outlaws
than servants to wipe my shit.

135
00:13:17.846 --> 00:13:19.280
Take care. fool.

136
00:13:19.381 --> 00:13:21.982
You're not scrubbing
a floor.

137
00:13:22.083 --> 00:13:23.851
<i>Mes plus sincères excuses.</i>
<i>mon Leige.</i>

138
00:13:36.297 --> 00:13:38.465
Brother Wilk.

139
00:13:45.541 --> 00:13:47.642
We've heard from our friends
in Glen Darby Birch.

140
00:13:47.742 --> 00:13:49.342
Ventris comes again. Collectors.

141
00:13:49.943 --> 00:13:51.744
- Already?
- More brutal than ever.

142
00:13:51.845 --> 00:13:53.746
Doubled the tax.
doubled the guards.

143
00:13:53.847 --> 00:13:55.748
They'll be at
our door by daybreak.

144
00:13:55.849 --> 00:13:58.251
Our journey is longer
traveling off the main trails.

145
00:13:58.352 --> 00:14:00.787
We need to ride now if we want
to catch them in darkness.

146
00:14:04.692 --> 00:14:06.560
His troops will be ready for us.

147
00:14:06.661 --> 00:14:08.494
The risk grows too great.

148
00:14:08.595 --> 00:14:11.930
They'll take what little stock
and harvest we have left.

149
00:14:12.031 --> 00:14:14.466
A winter of starvation
is the greater risk.

150
00:14:19.906 --> 00:14:21.807
We can't do this without you.

151
00:14:27.313 --> 00:14:28.379
Yea.

152
00:14:28.480 --> 00:14:30.215
Gather supplies.

153
00:14:30.316 --> 00:14:31.982
We'll need to ride
before midday.

154
00:14:32.084 --> 00:14:33.751
- I want to fight. Wilk.
- No. Ash.

155
00:14:33.852 --> 00:14:35.286
- You're of better use here.
- But I'm of proper age.

156
00:14:35.387 --> 00:14:36.887
It's a proper mind
we're in need of.

157
00:14:36.988 --> 00:14:38.055
I'm clever.

158
00:14:38.156 --> 00:14:39.457
Please. I want to help.

159
00:14:39.558 --> 00:14:40.891
If we need to make haste

160
00:14:40.992 --> 00:14:42.660
off beaten paths.
no one knows the woods

161
00:14:42.761 --> 00:14:44.495
- better than our clever trapper.
- Yeah. True.

162
00:14:44.597 --> 00:14:48.164
I know every twig from
here to the sea caverns.

163
00:14:48.266 --> 00:14:50.667
- Please.
- You can ride with us.

164
00:14:50.768 --> 00:14:52.669
but you don't fight.
And the sheep stays here.

165
00:14:52.770 --> 00:14:54.871
I get a hood though. right?

166
00:14:54.972 --> 00:14:57.140
Yea. I'll make you one
out of sheepskin.

167
00:14:57.242 --> 00:14:58.975
You can leave Miriam

168
00:14:59.076 --> 00:15:00.944
in our pen;
she'll be safe there.

169
00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:03.680
You're a cruel one.
Toran Prichard.

170
00:15:03.782 --> 00:15:06.883
He's tupping mindless beasts.
and I'm the cruel one?

171
00:15:08.685 --> 00:15:10.019
Come on.

172
00:15:10.121 --> 00:15:12.055
Come on there. boys.

173
00:15:26.370 --> 00:15:27.570
I know that look.

174
00:15:27.671 --> 00:15:29.272
You should.

175
00:15:29.373 --> 00:15:31.274
I wear it often.

176
00:15:31.375 --> 00:15:34.610
Ventris is sly and brutal.

177
00:15:34.711 --> 00:15:37.280
It's only time and chance
before you feel his blade.

178
00:15:37.381 --> 00:15:40.516
You're not a
rebel. Wilkin.

179
00:15:40.617 --> 00:15:42.518
Let the band of Byth Encil

180
00:15:42.619 --> 00:15:44.519
take their defiant
vengeance to our baron.

181
00:15:44.620 --> 00:15:47.289
This isn't about vengeance.

182
00:15:47.390 --> 00:15:48.723
You heard your father.

183
00:15:48.824 --> 00:15:51.393
We take this risk

184
00:15:51.494 --> 00:15:53.094
to survive.

185
00:15:53.195 --> 00:15:55.930
The baron's tax leech
comes twice a season now.

186
00:15:56.031 --> 00:15:57.632
We've barely stock
and food to live.

187
00:15:57.733 --> 00:16:01.803
You're the only stock
I can't live without!

188
00:16:08.643 --> 00:16:10.644
Good morning. farmer.

189
00:16:15.517 --> 00:16:18.118
Fair dame.

190
00:16:18.219 --> 00:16:20.654
And how is our gentle
lytling doing today?

191
00:16:20.755 --> 00:16:22.623
Very active.

192
00:16:22.724 --> 00:16:23.889
Hmm.

193
00:16:23.990 --> 00:16:26.125
A life eager

194
00:16:26.226 --> 00:16:28.894
to begin a greater journey.

195
00:16:31.332 --> 00:16:32.298
Yea.

196
00:16:32.399 --> 00:16:35.034
You must cover
this wound.

197
00:16:35.135 --> 00:16:38.805
The spill layer of the river
swims with sickness.

198
00:16:38.905 --> 00:16:40.873
I'm fine.

199
00:16:40.974 --> 00:16:43.007
And in
three days' time.

200
00:16:43.108 --> 00:16:44.909
you will be weak
and fevered.

201
00:16:46.912 --> 00:16:48.847
Boil these.

202
00:16:48.948 --> 00:16:51.383
Soak the wound
in the broth.

203
00:16:51.484 --> 00:16:52.884
Yea.

204
00:16:55.521 --> 00:16:57.556
Thank you.

205
00:17:13.938 --> 00:17:15.939
The other man.

206
00:17:22.012 --> 00:17:25.181
God has put him
on our path.

207
00:17:34.157 --> 00:17:37.326
Quarter rips for
the other two quaints.

208
00:17:37.428 --> 00:17:38.795
_

209
00:17:38.896 --> 00:17:40.263
It's double shillings
for that.

210
00:17:40.364 --> 00:17:43.099
Finish the task.

211
00:17:43.200 --> 00:17:44.967
Fair rate will follow.

212
00:17:59.649 --> 00:18:01.317
Did you soak the rag
in dumb paste?

213
00:18:01.418 --> 00:18:03.718
I... I...

214
00:18:03.819 --> 00:18:05.753
The pot wouldn't fit
in the bags. Father.

215
00:18:05.854 --> 00:18:07.588
But I can...

216
00:18:17.666 --> 00:18:19.600
Stupid and weak.

217
00:18:24.073 --> 00:18:26.074
Stupid and weak.

218
00:18:53.547 --> 00:18:56.416
God. I hate when she does that.

219
00:19:01.723 --> 00:19:03.690
Milady?

220
00:19:03.791 --> 00:19:05.258
Lady Love?

221
00:19:07.294 --> 00:19:08.495
Shit.

222
00:19:25.278 --> 00:19:28.080
Can you please
not do that. Love?

223
00:19:28.181 --> 00:19:30.850
My heart drowns
with you every time.

224
00:19:30.951 --> 00:19:34.019
I'm fine.
dear Isabel.

225
00:19:34.120 --> 00:19:37.189
I've been swimming in this
water since I was born.

226
00:19:37.290 --> 00:19:39.091
The chill refreshes
my spirit.

227
00:19:39.192 --> 00:19:40.892
Reminds me of
who I am.

228
00:19:40.994 --> 00:19:43.728
The baroness
who caught her death?

229
00:19:43.830 --> 00:19:48.067
The hopeful Welsh girl who
knows God holds her close.

230
00:19:48.168 --> 00:19:49.901
He has a journey in mind.

231
00:19:50.003 --> 00:19:51.236
Yes.

232
00:19:51.338 --> 00:19:53.505
I know that girl.

233
00:19:59.712 --> 00:20:01.913
Time is a most
aggressive foe. Milus.

234
00:20:02.014 --> 00:20:04.950
Favor of my rule
changes with the wind.

235
00:20:05.050 --> 00:20:07.619
The unrest that grows
on this damp rock...

236
00:20:07.720 --> 00:20:10.489
I need to make my gains
now. while I still hold

237
00:20:10.590 --> 00:20:12.990
the king's trust.

238
00:20:13.091 --> 00:20:15.058
Wealth. my lord.

239
00:20:15.159 --> 00:20:17.795
is the foundation
of any temple of power.

240
00:20:17.896 --> 00:20:20.163
We need to fortify
our resources.

241
00:20:20.264 --> 00:20:22.967
Steeper taxes and tariffs.

242
00:20:23.067 --> 00:20:24.368
Yes. agreed.

243
00:20:24.469 --> 00:20:27.237
Pardon. Lord Ventris.
good Chamberlain.

244
00:20:27.338 --> 00:20:29.740
Baron Pryce's emissary
waits for you at the market.

245
00:20:29.841 --> 00:20:31.642
He is... quite eager.

246
00:20:31.743 --> 00:20:34.844
I assume Pryce
sends no gifts

247
00:20:34.945 --> 00:20:36.480
with his eager
messenger?

248
00:20:36.580 --> 00:20:38.715
Gifts. Baron?

249
00:20:38.816 --> 00:20:40.984
Stuffed pheasant.
Aged wine.

250
00:20:41.085 --> 00:20:42.219
A bevy of
virgin whores.

251
00:20:42.320 --> 00:20:43.586
Why would he send such?

252
00:20:43.687 --> 00:20:45.522
Ballok cod.

253
00:20:45.623 --> 00:20:46.956
Why does he want an audience?

254
00:20:47.058 --> 00:20:48.058
Oh. yes.

255
00:20:48.159 --> 00:20:49.692
Again. he makes a heated point

256
00:20:49.793 --> 00:20:50.927
of the steep tariff.

257
00:20:51.029 --> 00:20:52.362
Asserts that Baron Pryce

258
00:20:52.463 --> 00:20:54.697
will refuse payment
if it grows again.

259
00:20:54.798 --> 00:20:56.799
If Pryce wants access to
the sea. he will pay for it.

260
00:20:56.901 --> 00:21:00.102
And if he refuses. then we
have cause to assert power.

261
00:21:00.203 --> 00:21:01.905
Into Pryceshire?

262
00:21:02.006 --> 00:21:04.807
But his legions outnumber ours.

263
00:21:04.909 --> 00:21:07.744
Pryce is a man
of books.

264
00:21:07.845 --> 00:21:10.312
Thinkers die
in battle.

265
00:21:10.414 --> 00:21:12.881
Good Baron.

266
00:21:12.982 --> 00:21:14.683
Chamberlain.

267
00:21:17.153 --> 00:21:19.555
What is our passage
for today. Father?

268
00:21:19.656 --> 00:21:22.457
Genesis.

269
00:21:22.559 --> 00:21:26.127
We're learning how
God created us in his likeness.

270
00:21:26.228 --> 00:21:28.329
Gave us a perfect world.

271
00:21:30.733 --> 00:21:33.501
Care to join us. Baron?

272
00:21:35.070 --> 00:21:37.705
Yes.

273
00:21:38.740 --> 00:21:40.808
Another time. Father.

274
00:21:50.418 --> 00:21:51.886
And what of our king?

275
00:21:51.987 --> 00:21:54.388
Where will Edward sit
in this dispute with you

276
00:21:54.489 --> 00:21:55.755
and Baron Pryce?

277
00:21:55.856 --> 00:21:57.924
Where his soft French
bottom always sits--

278
00:21:58.025 --> 00:21:59.526
in the middle.

279
00:21:59.627 --> 00:22:02.662
waiting like a flowered
girl to coo the victor.

280
00:22:02.763 --> 00:22:05.399
With a mouth
full of noble seed.

281
00:22:07.535 --> 00:22:09.736
Ah. yes.
Because he's a bit fancy.

282
00:22:31.358 --> 00:22:33.658
Tell Pryce's man

283
00:22:33.759 --> 00:22:35.660
the tariff
just went up again.

284
00:22:35.761 --> 00:22:37.061
A third?

285
00:22:37.163 --> 00:22:39.464
More than fair.

286
00:22:39.565 --> 00:22:42.267
But. my lord. you...
you realize you taunt him

287
00:22:42.368 --> 00:22:43.502
by raising it
yet again?

288
00:22:43.603 --> 00:22:45.237
The taunt <i>is</i> the message.

289
00:22:45.338 --> 00:22:47.972
Deliver it.

290
00:22:48.073 --> 00:22:50.108
Yes. Sorry.

291
00:22:50.209 --> 00:22:52.210
Baron. Chamberlain.

292
00:22:54.713 --> 00:22:56.280
Hello. sir.

293
00:22:56.381 --> 00:22:57.949
Your young brother
doubts our methods.

294
00:22:58.050 --> 00:23:00.284
Half my blood.

295
00:23:00.385 --> 00:23:02.219
Quarter the brains.

296
00:23:12.997 --> 00:23:14.631
Hey.

297
00:23:14.732 --> 00:23:16.900
Give it here.
You carried Da's ax last ride.

298
00:23:17.001 --> 00:23:18.902
Yeah. because you don't have
the arm to swing it. puny-kin.

299
00:23:19.003 --> 00:23:20.236
Says you. you fat elf.

300
00:23:23.941 --> 00:23:25.608
Oh. hey. hey.
whoa. whoa. whoa. hey!

301
00:23:27.345 --> 00:23:30.080
Will you two
ever grow up?

302
00:23:33.483 --> 00:23:36.552
You should be whittling me toys.
not playing hero. old man.

303
00:23:36.653 --> 00:23:41.456
Whittling is for the lame
of mind. motherly daughter.

304
00:23:43.393 --> 00:23:45.327
Be certain that's not
how you return.

305
00:23:51.734 --> 00:23:53.768
No need to wear
the funeral mask.

306
00:23:53.869 --> 00:23:55.203
I'm not dead yet. wife.

307
00:23:55.304 --> 00:23:56.604
The mask is for me.

308
00:23:56.706 --> 00:23:59.607
You'll be the death of me.
you reckless poke.

309
00:23:59.709 --> 00:24:01.710
Hey.

310
00:24:03.545 --> 00:24:05.113
You keep her heavy on the
mead while I'm away. boy.

311
00:24:05.214 --> 00:24:06.114
She's bearable that way.

312
00:24:06.215 --> 00:24:08.649
Am I a ghost without ears?

313
00:24:08.751 --> 00:24:10.650
I will. Da.
Heaps of it.

314
00:24:36.176 --> 00:24:38.144
We'll be back
before half moon.

315
00:24:38.245 --> 00:24:39.545
Yea.

316
00:24:39.646 --> 00:24:42.215
I'll be here. Twice the cow.

317
00:24:45.285 --> 00:24:46.886
You stay in there.

318
00:24:46.987 --> 00:24:48.887
No catching your mother
with a sneakish birth.

319
00:24:48.988 --> 00:24:50.521
Running the laws
of nature now. farmer?

320
00:24:50.623 --> 00:24:52.157
Never. dear Eva.

321
00:24:52.258 --> 00:24:55.127
I leave the control of
all things earthly to the women.

322
00:25:00.366 --> 00:25:02.000
God keep you safe.

323
00:25:02.101 --> 00:25:03.168
Always.

324
00:25:03.269 --> 00:25:04.770
Hup.

325
00:25:04.871 --> 00:25:05.804
Hup!

326
00:25:27.700 --> 00:25:33.379
_

327
00:26:20.422 --> 00:26:22.157
We meet again. tax man!

328
00:26:26.128 --> 00:26:29.297
Oh. please. Oh. please.

329
00:26:29.398 --> 00:26:30.865
Spare me still.

330
00:26:34.603 --> 00:26:35.736
Tell your greedy lord.

331
00:26:35.837 --> 00:26:38.606
if he keeps biting
like the boar.

332
00:26:38.707 --> 00:26:40.174
we keep laying the traps.

333
00:26:41.676 --> 00:26:42.944
Where's your horse.
tax man?!

334
00:27:01.162 --> 00:27:03.597
Here.

335
00:27:03.698 --> 00:27:07.567
Yeah. it is true. friend.

336
00:27:07.668 --> 00:27:10.603
I'll own skill of this one day.

337
00:27:10.704 --> 00:27:13.606
I'll make my little wings
that vanish on the bark.

338
00:27:13.707 --> 00:27:15.274
I will fly.

339
00:27:16.977 --> 00:27:18.411
Woden has promised me.

340
00:27:20.448 --> 00:27:23.015
Ah. my friends return.

341
00:27:31.658 --> 00:27:33.058
Yah!

342
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:44.203
Bag the chattel and furs.

343
00:27:55.715 --> 00:27:58.680
_

344
00:28:08.894 --> 00:28:13.164
Destiny has met
your ambitious young warrior.

345
00:28:13.265 --> 00:28:17.001
Wilkin Brattle will no longer
draw favor from the king.

346
00:28:17.102 --> 00:28:19.636
The long blades
of the Scots served us well.

347
00:28:19.738 --> 00:28:22.673
An inspired plan.
good Marshal.

348
00:28:26.144 --> 00:28:28.079
Send troops
for the bodies.

349
00:28:28.180 --> 00:28:32.149
If we bring him back. Constable.

350
00:28:32.250 --> 00:28:34.151
Brattle will be seen
as a slain hero

351
00:28:34.252 --> 00:28:36.186
who stood up
to an army of Scots.

352
00:28:39.190 --> 00:28:41.191
They will immortalize him.

353
00:28:43.227 --> 00:28:45.028
Perhaps we take comfort

354
00:28:45.129 --> 00:28:48.464
knowing that we serve
God's hungry creatures.

355
00:28:48.565 --> 00:28:50.299
Yes.

356
00:28:50.400 --> 00:28:51.901
Feast on. my friends!

357
00:28:52.002 --> 00:28:53.737
King-fed meat!

358
00:29:33.509 --> 00:29:35.510
Forgive me.

359
00:29:40.475 --> 00:29:45.490
_

360
00:29:45.492 --> 00:29:47.493
Baron Pryce.

361
00:29:48.663 --> 00:29:50.063
Pardon. my lord.

362
00:29:50.164 --> 00:29:51.832
Your emissary has returned
from Ventrishire.

363
00:29:54.302 --> 00:29:56.102
Finish with disbursement.
Chamberlain.

364
00:29:56.203 --> 00:29:57.504
Of course.

365
00:29:57.605 --> 00:29:59.472
Edwin.

366
00:29:59.573 --> 00:30:01.607
It is much too damp
in this room.

367
00:30:01.708 --> 00:30:02.608
Yes. my love.

368
00:30:04.211 --> 00:30:06.546
Take the baroness
to the sun room.

369
00:30:20.394 --> 00:30:21.794
Who's next?

370
00:30:21.895 --> 00:30:23.763
Gawain Maddox!

371
00:30:27.267 --> 00:30:29.201
The traveling punisher.

372
00:30:29.302 --> 00:30:30.670
Ah.

373
00:30:47.954 --> 00:30:50.755
You claimed fairness.

374
00:30:50.857 --> 00:30:52.191
This is half my wage.

375
00:30:52.292 --> 00:30:53.925
Do you know
how many journeymen

376
00:30:54.027 --> 00:30:56.928
pass through this shire
every week. hmm?

377
00:30:57.030 --> 00:31:01.066
Blacksmiths. bowmen. even
executioners such as yourself.

378
00:31:03.103 --> 00:31:06.105
Many flee the South
in search of work.

379
00:31:06.206 --> 00:31:08.540
That doesn't mean we don't
deserve our rightful pay.

380
00:31:08.641 --> 00:31:13.344
If you do not find this
satisfactory. move on.

381
00:31:13.445 --> 00:31:15.514
Find yourself another
shire where you can

382
00:31:15.615 --> 00:31:17.782
peddle your brutal gifts.

383
00:31:19.151 --> 00:31:20.519
Next.

384
00:31:20.620 --> 00:31:21.520
Barclay the minstrel.

385
00:31:21.621 --> 00:31:24.489
Ah. the minstrel.

386
00:31:29.028 --> 00:31:30.929
We travel.

387
00:31:31.030 --> 00:31:32.997
But where to. Maddy?

388
00:31:33.097 --> 00:31:35.165
To the sea.

389
00:31:35.266 --> 00:31:36.934
Ventrishire.

390
00:31:37.035 --> 00:31:38.368
Now!

391
00:31:46.444 --> 00:31:48.679
Forgive us. Baron.

392
00:31:48.780 --> 00:31:49.880
My lady.

393
00:31:49.981 --> 00:31:51.715
There's been
another attack.

394
00:31:51.816 --> 00:31:52.983
Hooded thieves.

395
00:31:53.084 --> 00:31:54.451
All eight of
our men slain.

396
00:31:56.421 --> 00:31:57.754
Took us in darkness.

397
00:31:57.855 --> 00:31:58.855
Deadly ghosts.

398
00:31:58.956 --> 00:32:00.590
- The same ones?
- Yes.

399
00:32:00.691 --> 00:32:02.592
Six. in familiar hoods.

400
00:32:02.693 --> 00:32:04.928
There was another this time.
deeper in the woods.

401
00:32:05.029 --> 00:32:06.530
Saw a flash of his face.

402
00:32:06.630 --> 00:32:07.564
A young one.

403
00:32:07.665 --> 00:32:08.865
How do you know he was a bandit?

404
00:32:08.966 --> 00:32:10.233
He was hooded.

405
00:32:10.334 --> 00:32:11.701
His clothing was different.

406
00:32:11.802 --> 00:32:15.271
all hides and furs.
but he was with them.

407
00:32:15.372 --> 00:32:16.573
Uh. a watcher perhaps.

408
00:32:16.674 --> 00:32:18.074
What kind of fur did he wear?

409
00:32:18.175 --> 00:32:20.810
It had sheen--
uh. beaver pelt. I'd say.

410
00:32:22.245 --> 00:32:25.748
Costly vesture
for a peasant bandit.

411
00:32:25.849 --> 00:32:28.985
Beavers.

412
00:32:29.086 --> 00:32:31.420
What rivers do they dam?

413
00:32:31.521 --> 00:32:32.421
I'm not sure.

414
00:32:32.522 --> 00:32:34.991
Colder ones. perhaps.

415
00:32:35.092 --> 00:32:37.093
West to the sea.

416
00:32:38.595 --> 00:32:41.564
West.

417
00:32:41.664 --> 00:32:43.399
Gwynedd and the minor turns.

418
00:32:43.500 --> 00:32:44.633
Here.

419
00:32:44.734 --> 00:32:47.069
Branches of the Dunoding
run west.

420
00:32:47.170 --> 00:32:48.904
Touch the far end
of the shire.

421
00:32:49.005 --> 00:32:50.906
We've settlers there?

422
00:32:51.007 --> 00:32:52.475
No. I think...

423
00:32:52.576 --> 00:32:53.509
Yes.

424
00:32:53.610 --> 00:32:55.311
Yes. we do.

425
00:32:55.412 --> 00:32:57.045
Barley farmers.

426
00:32:57.147 --> 00:32:58.981
West River Riding.

427
00:32:59.082 --> 00:33:00.983
Quarterly collections.

428
00:33:01.084 --> 00:33:02.817
Oh. West River.

429
00:33:02.918 --> 00:33:04.219
Yes. of course.

430
00:33:04.320 --> 00:33:05.653
Half legion and
horsemen. my charge.

431
00:33:05.754 --> 00:33:06.954
You ride with us.

432
00:33:07.055 --> 00:33:08.389
Pick out the watcher.

433
00:33:08.491 --> 00:33:09.457
Make sound guesses
of the others

434
00:33:09.558 --> 00:33:12.026
without their clever hoods.

435
00:33:12.128 --> 00:33:14.061
You as well. Reeve.

436
00:33:14.163 --> 00:33:16.231
Get to know your shire.

437
00:33:16.332 --> 00:33:17.465
Yes. dear brother.

438
00:33:17.566 --> 00:33:19.501
Baron. My lady.

439
00:33:25.008 --> 00:33:27.441
And what of manor law?

440
00:33:27.542 --> 00:33:30.477
Is there a mind for fairness
in your swift purpose?

441
00:33:31.813 --> 00:33:33.547
Of course. my love.

442
00:33:33.648 --> 00:33:35.582
Fair process for every man.

443
00:33:43.158 --> 00:33:45.392
I know your distress
is undoubtedly

444
00:33:45.493 --> 00:33:49.396
about the safety
of your husband. my lady.

445
00:33:49.497 --> 00:33:51.597
but an ignorant eye
may see it

446
00:33:51.699 --> 00:33:54.467
as concern
for the welfare of outlaws.

447
00:33:54.568 --> 00:33:56.903
Well. I thank my maker
that I'm in the presence

448
00:33:57.004 --> 00:33:59.939
of a man who never leans
towards ignorance.

449
00:34:02.009 --> 00:34:04.010
Indeed.

450
00:34:04.111 --> 00:34:05.812
Knowledge is my service.

451
00:34:05.913 --> 00:34:08.281
Indeed.

452
00:34:08.382 --> 00:34:12.251
Perhaps you should share some of
that knowledge with my husband.

453
00:34:12.352 --> 00:34:14.687
Let him know that his thirst
to grow this shire

454
00:34:14.788 --> 00:34:16.522
should not be quenched

455
00:34:16.623 --> 00:34:19.625
with the sweat and blood
of its own people.

456
00:34:19.726 --> 00:34:23.596
It is the people's duty
to tithe.

457
00:34:23.697 --> 00:34:25.264
Only rebels

458
00:34:25.365 --> 00:34:27.266
refuse to honor
the rule of law.

459
00:34:27.367 --> 00:34:29.001
No commoner wants rebellion.

460
00:34:29.102 --> 00:34:32.471
It only comes after hope and
reason are burned to the ground.

461
00:34:32.573 --> 00:34:35.074
Tell me. Baroness.

462
00:34:35.175 --> 00:34:38.076
How is it that someone
of your privilege

463
00:34:38.177 --> 00:34:41.446
may come to know
the plight of the common man?

464
00:34:43.516 --> 00:34:46.718
Well. unlike some
within these walls.

465
00:34:46.819 --> 00:34:49.854
I live with open eyes
and open heart.

466
00:34:52.592 --> 00:34:55.193
You will break them. Milus.

467
00:34:55.294 --> 00:34:57.095
And we both know
there's nothing more dangerous

468
00:34:57.196 --> 00:35:00.532
than a Welshman
who has nothing to lose.

469
00:35:09.041 --> 00:35:12.743
Keep my husband to a safe path.

470
00:35:12.844 --> 00:35:16.580
I'm depending on you.
good Chamberlain.

471
00:35:37.759 --> 00:35:41.937
_

472
00:35:50.881 --> 00:35:53.816
Melt it down. and you
shall have whatever you like.

473
00:36:02.192 --> 00:36:04.827
Our brave hunters approach.

474
00:36:04.928 --> 00:36:05.894
Midshire hares!

475
00:36:05.995 --> 00:36:08.397
Big enough to mount.

476
00:36:08.498 --> 00:36:09.864
We want to skewer them
with sticks.

477
00:36:09.965 --> 00:36:11.366
not with our pricks.
you beast-lover.

478
00:36:13.436 --> 00:36:15.337
Don't listen to him. boy.

479
00:36:15.438 --> 00:36:18.407
We take our comfort
wherever we find it.

480
00:36:18.508 --> 00:36:20.442
And what if you find him
taking comfort in your pen...

481
00:36:21.644 --> 00:36:23.044
...poking your prize hog?

482
00:36:24.647 --> 00:36:26.380
I don't fancy hogs.

483
00:36:27.883 --> 00:36:29.784
That's true.
He's a one-sheep man.

484
00:36:40.763 --> 00:36:42.797
Why does Wilk
use oak and not a blade?

485
00:36:46.035 --> 00:36:48.202
There are many things

486
00:36:48.303 --> 00:36:51.038
we do not know about our leader.

487
00:36:51.140 --> 00:36:52.140
Even Petra knows
little of his life

488
00:36:52.241 --> 00:36:53.241
before he came to the river.

489
00:36:53.342 --> 00:36:55.409
Had to be a soldier.

490
00:36:55.511 --> 00:36:57.978
The fight skill
he's given you--

491
00:36:58.079 --> 00:37:00.581
that was learned on a field
of battle. not barley.

492
00:37:00.682 --> 00:37:03.651
We've all tales
best kept locked in our head.

493
00:37:08.089 --> 00:37:09.690
More of your song.

494
00:37:13.962 --> 00:37:18.431
♪ ye talisman give potion... ♪

495
00:37:18.533 --> 00:37:20.500
You should eat.

496
00:37:20.601 --> 00:37:22.502
Yea.

497
00:37:27.709 --> 00:37:29.943
Ventris will keep
doubling his guards.

498
00:37:30.045 --> 00:37:31.879
Yeah. we can't
do this alone anymore.

499
00:37:34.082 --> 00:37:35.716
You saw the daffodil hides
in the trees.

500
00:37:35.817 --> 00:37:37.685
The Byth Encil rebels
would welcome our skill.

501
00:37:37.786 --> 00:37:39.719
I can arrange for a meet.
and we can...

502
00:37:39.820 --> 00:37:44.323
I serve God and family.
not cause or crown.

503
00:37:44.425 --> 00:37:46.325
Give straight.
brother.

504
00:37:46.427 --> 00:37:48.595
You think the gates of
heaven will fly open

505
00:37:48.696 --> 00:37:50.930
because you down a man
with wood instead of steel?

506
00:37:51.031 --> 00:37:52.064
Perhaps not.

507
00:37:52.165 --> 00:37:54.401
We've both watched men die

508
00:37:54.502 --> 00:37:57.236
by the work of our hands.
Wilkin.

509
00:37:57.337 --> 00:38:01.641
In service of gods or king.
it doesn't matter.

510
00:38:01.742 --> 00:38:03.810
We're driven by
a deeper burn.

511
00:38:03.911 --> 00:38:07.514
and we need to feel that
or we wither.

512
00:38:44.850 --> 00:38:46.851
Where's your man?!

513
00:38:46.953 --> 00:38:48.553
Where's your right?

514
00:39:01.033 --> 00:39:02.434
No farmer here.

515
00:39:02.534 --> 00:39:03.568
Only women

516
00:39:03.669 --> 00:39:05.270
and useless elders.

517
00:39:05.371 --> 00:39:07.604
Where are your men?!

518
00:39:13.311 --> 00:39:14.744
They're hunting.

519
00:39:14.846 --> 00:39:16.246
Lord Ventris.

520
00:39:16.348 --> 00:39:18.648
Skins for the
next harvest.

521
00:39:20.986 --> 00:39:22.919
In the dark?

522
00:39:23.021 --> 00:39:25.289
Do I seem a fool?

523
00:39:30.928 --> 00:39:32.762
Slit the boy's throat.

524
00:39:32.864 --> 00:39:35.298
No! No! No!

525
00:39:35.399 --> 00:39:36.900
Stop! Stop!

526
00:39:37.001 --> 00:39:39.302
Where are they?

527
00:39:39.403 --> 00:39:41.671
A lie bleeds two throats.

528
00:39:42.940 --> 00:39:45.074
They...

529
00:39:45.175 --> 00:39:47.243
they went to Glen Darby Birch.

530
00:39:47.344 --> 00:39:49.445
With their hoods?

531
00:39:55.019 --> 00:39:56.652
Yea! With hoods!

532
00:39:56.753 --> 00:39:58.087
How many?

533
00:39:58.188 --> 00:39:59.188
Seven.

534
00:39:59.289 --> 00:40:00.856
You expect your baron
to believe

535
00:40:00.957 --> 00:40:03.126
that a pox-dowed band of farmers

536
00:40:03.227 --> 00:40:05.794
have skill enough
to knell our noble ranks?

537
00:40:05.896 --> 00:40:07.130
He should.

538
00:40:07.231 --> 00:40:08.731
His ranks

539
00:40:08.832 --> 00:40:11.434
seem only fit to strike
women and children!

540
00:40:29.118 --> 00:40:30.585
Kill them all.

541
00:40:32.588 --> 00:40:34.056
Burn it to the ground.

542
00:40:34.157 --> 00:40:35.990
You devils!

543
00:40:36.092 --> 00:40:38.026
You curs!

544
00:40:38.127 --> 00:40:42.464
They will hunt you down
and cut out your stone hearts!

545
00:40:42.565 --> 00:40:45.933
Make this one a sight
for deep memory.

546
00:40:46.034 --> 00:40:47.634
Brutal.

547
00:40:47.735 --> 00:40:49.937
Let it strike a pain
that cannot be hidden

548
00:40:50.038 --> 00:40:51.972
with insolent hoods.

549
00:40:52.074 --> 00:40:53.907
Run. Petra!

550
00:40:55.510 --> 00:40:57.445
Fetch her!

551
00:41:07.821 --> 00:41:09.789
This is a breach of law.

552
00:41:09.890 --> 00:41:11.591
Both God and king.

553
00:41:11.692 --> 00:41:12.725
It-it...

554
00:41:12.826 --> 00:41:15.995
This is madness!

555
00:41:16.097 --> 00:41:18.931
Please. my lord.
Please.

556
00:41:19.032 --> 00:41:23.470
Relieve our collector
of his moral conflict.

557
00:42:01.373 --> 00:42:03.374
I beg of you. Please!

558
00:42:03.475 --> 00:42:05.209
Find the God you defend.

559
00:42:05.310 --> 00:42:06.577
Have mercy. please.

560
00:42:06.678 --> 00:42:08.579
Not for me.
but for the innocent heart

561
00:42:08.680 --> 00:42:10.948
beating inside. please.

562
00:42:11.049 --> 00:42:14.619
Please.

563
00:42:14.719 --> 00:42:16.954
Please.

564
00:42:43.648 --> 00:42:45.916
Run.

565
00:42:46.017 --> 00:42:48.318
And don't ever come back here.
not anywhere in this shire.

566
00:42:48.419 --> 00:42:49.753
You'll be sure as dead.

567
00:42:49.854 --> 00:42:51.755
Go!

568
00:43:53.482 --> 00:43:55.550
The farmers will see the smoke.

569
00:43:55.651 --> 00:43:57.652
They won't ride
into a waiting attack.

570
00:43:57.754 --> 00:43:59.855
I want them alive.

571
00:43:59.956 --> 00:44:01.522
For now.

572
00:44:01.624 --> 00:44:03.991
Let them suffer this.

573
00:44:26.581 --> 00:44:29.483
You... you.

574
00:44:29.584 --> 00:44:31.518
What are you...?

575
00:45:03.962 --> 00:45:06.733
_

576
00:45:11.177 --> 00:45:12.844
Careful. boy.

577
00:45:12.945 --> 00:45:15.881
S-Sorry. Ma.

578
00:45:21.287 --> 00:45:24.355
It's shit. Hmm?

579
00:45:24.457 --> 00:45:26.256
Like the lot of you.

580
00:45:26.357 --> 00:45:28.693
- Come here.
- I'm-I'm sorry.

581
00:45:28.794 --> 00:45:31.094
Don't mother him.

582
00:45:31.195 --> 00:45:34.064
He needs to feel the pain
of his mistake.

583
00:45:34.164 --> 00:45:35.899
He feels it.

584
00:45:36.000 --> 00:45:38.735
I won't tend it.

585
00:45:38.836 --> 00:45:42.105
Please. enjoy the drink.

586
00:45:42.206 --> 00:45:43.974
We have another bird.

587
00:45:44.075 --> 00:45:45.809
I'll feed you
in short.

588
00:45:45.910 --> 00:45:48.177
Don't put rule on me. whore!

589
00:45:49.980 --> 00:45:51.614
No.

590
00:45:51.715 --> 00:45:52.915
Crawl. you cur!

591
00:45:53.016 --> 00:45:54.517
Please. Maddy.

592
00:45:54.618 --> 00:45:56.319
Show me the trench.

593
00:46:02.892 --> 00:46:04.293
The village!

594
00:46:04.394 --> 00:46:06.695
Hyah!

595
00:46:26.449 --> 00:46:27.649
No.

596
00:46:30.418 --> 00:46:32.386
No.

597
00:47:14.527 --> 00:47:16.261
Dear child.

598
00:47:29.474 --> 00:47:31.475
Oh...

599
00:47:48.260 --> 00:47:50.560
Sweet boy.

600
00:47:55.066 --> 00:47:57.400
My Rhys.

601
00:48:02.140 --> 00:48:04.541
This was Ventris.

602
00:48:04.642 --> 00:48:06.877
His collector as proof!

603
00:48:06.978 --> 00:48:09.379
Savage noble!

604
00:48:15.152 --> 00:48:17.721
Damn your holy destiny.

605
00:48:22.326 --> 00:48:25.128
Devil Christ. Damn you.

606
00:49:20.015 --> 00:49:21.749
The sword.

607
00:49:23.919 --> 00:49:26.421
Crest of Edward the First.

608
00:49:32.393 --> 00:49:34.361
Where does he ride?

609
00:49:34.462 --> 00:49:36.430
To meet the devil.

610
00:49:36.531 --> 00:49:38.898
As are we.

611
00:49:38.999 --> 00:49:40.634
Our families...

612
00:49:40.735 --> 00:49:42.636
Will be avenged.

613
00:49:42.737 --> 00:49:44.538
Hup!

614
00:49:57.784 --> 00:50:00.053
See to the dead.

615
00:50:00.154 --> 00:50:01.620
This is my fight.

616
00:50:01.722 --> 00:50:04.357
We've all earned this horror.

617
00:50:09.162 --> 00:50:12.698
I've no plan but vengeance.

618
00:50:12.799 --> 00:50:15.368
The only plan left.

619
00:50:26.913 --> 00:50:28.480
Yea. then.

620
00:50:28.581 --> 00:50:30.314
To Castle Ventris.

621
00:50:30.416 --> 00:50:31.916
Ha!

622
00:50:58.810 --> 00:51:01.445
This is mine.

623
00:51:06.084 --> 00:51:07.785
My due.

624
00:51:07.886 --> 00:51:10.922
My sorrow.

625
00:51:16.028 --> 00:51:18.238
Forgive me.

626
00:51:41.250 --> 00:51:43.685
The witch.

627
00:51:51.027 --> 00:51:52.994
What brings you so far east.

628
00:51:53.095 --> 00:51:54.829
woman?

629
00:51:54.931 --> 00:51:57.799
The same thing
that brings all of you.

630
00:51:57.900 --> 00:52:00.068
We flee the darkness.

631
00:52:00.169 --> 00:52:02.637
Did you witness the massacre?

632
00:52:02.738 --> 00:52:04.639
No.

633
00:52:04.740 --> 00:52:09.009
But I will witness yours
unless you alter your purpose.

634
00:52:09.110 --> 00:52:11.979
There's nothing to alter.

635
00:52:12.080 --> 00:52:13.713
We face what's ahead.

636
00:52:13.815 --> 00:52:18.652
But you do not need
to face it alone.

637
00:52:18.753 --> 00:52:23.257
Your cynic-- he has ties
to the way of victory.

638
00:52:33.367 --> 00:52:36.903
You are all knots and coil.

639
00:52:38.506 --> 00:52:41.240
Pain of yesterday's
fierce effort.

640
00:52:44.679 --> 00:52:47.080
So you found your bandits.

641
00:52:47.181 --> 00:52:49.048
No.

642
00:52:49.149 --> 00:52:51.985
But we met with the
proof of their guilt.

643
00:52:53.988 --> 00:52:55.955
And you've returned
with that proof?

644
00:52:58.658 --> 00:53:01.461
Difficult to carry
bone and slag.

645
00:53:02.796 --> 00:53:04.797
My lord.

646
00:53:04.898 --> 00:53:07.033
A scout came through from
midshire this morning.

647
00:53:07.134 --> 00:53:09.767
Spotted seven men
traveling east last night.

648
00:53:09.869 --> 00:53:12.604
One with a sword
bearing Longshanks' mark.

649
00:53:12.705 --> 00:53:14.606
Our bandits on a
mission. perhaps.

650
00:53:14.707 --> 00:53:17.042
Taking their vengeance
to my gate?

651
00:53:17.143 --> 00:53:19.478
Are they that mad with grief?

652
00:53:19.578 --> 00:53:22.981
Or soldiers willing to die
in service of their sorrow.

653
00:53:23.082 --> 00:53:25.150
I think it best
we meet them in journey.

654
00:53:25.251 --> 00:53:28.487
away from anyone who may see
this fool play as valiant.

655
00:53:28.587 --> 00:53:29.921
Stay.

656
00:53:30.023 --> 00:53:32.090
Protect the walls.

657
00:53:32.191 --> 00:53:33.824
Prepare a full legion
of foot soldiers.

658
00:53:33.925 --> 00:53:36.093
I'll gut this warrior bandit.

659
00:53:36.194 --> 00:53:38.795
Choke him cold with a snare
of his own entrails.

660
00:53:38.897 --> 00:53:40.831
A fine plan. my lord.

661
00:53:44.536 --> 00:53:46.937
Are you waiting
for a royal proclamation?

662
00:53:47.039 --> 00:53:48.605
Go with him. Reeve.

663
00:53:48.706 --> 00:53:50.874
Yes. indeed.
Chamberlain.

664
00:53:50.975 --> 00:53:52.309
My lady.

665
00:54:16.701 --> 00:54:19.036
Who are you. traveler?

666
00:54:19.136 --> 00:54:21.037
Gawain Maddox. milord.

667
00:54:21.137 --> 00:54:22.772
I come up from the South.

668
00:54:22.873 --> 00:54:24.607
Punisher by trade.

669
00:54:24.708 --> 00:54:26.642
You have tools in possession?

670
00:54:26.743 --> 00:54:28.210
Yea'on.

671
00:54:28.311 --> 00:54:29.645
Ride with us.

672
00:54:29.746 --> 00:54:32.281
I may need
your services.

673
00:54:32.382 --> 00:54:34.550
My family.

674
00:54:34.651 --> 00:54:36.052
Ride the main trail north.

675
00:54:36.152 --> 00:54:37.987
It leads to Castle Ventris.

676
00:54:38.088 --> 00:54:40.022
They can wait there.

677
00:54:42.024 --> 00:54:43.992
Just follow on.

678
00:54:44.093 --> 00:54:46.027
I'll be with you.

679
00:55:07.549 --> 00:55:11.385
Do you remember me.
Earl Constable?

680
00:55:13.422 --> 00:55:15.423
I'm the knight
you sent to his death

681
00:55:15.524 --> 00:55:18.726
at the hands
of the hoarding Scots.

682
00:55:19.760 --> 00:55:21.661
Impossible.

683
00:55:21.762 --> 00:55:25.231
You know this man. my lord?

684
00:55:25.333 --> 00:55:28.601
If you are indeed
that knight.

685
00:55:28.703 --> 00:55:32.271
you're either a
deserter or a ghost.

686
00:55:32.373 --> 00:55:35.642
If not dead then.

687
00:55:35.743 --> 00:55:37.677
then dead now.

688
00:55:43.416 --> 00:55:47.353
I live with the terror
of your betrayal every day.

689
00:55:50.157 --> 00:55:54.093
But I'll spare you that pain.

690
00:55:54.194 --> 00:55:57.029
Death will quiet your mind.

691
00:56:06.138 --> 00:56:08.206
They're all rebels. milord.

692
00:56:10.577 --> 00:56:13.912
Time to go back to hell.
Marcher Baron!

693
00:56:20.553 --> 00:56:23.488
<i>Deus vult!</i>

694
00:57:19.842 --> 00:57:21.008
Go. go. go!

695
00:58:40.619 --> 00:58:44.555
Not ghost. nor deserter.

696
00:58:44.656 --> 00:58:47.424
Nor hood.

697
00:59:26.396 --> 00:59:28.095
London will hunt down

698
00:59:28.196 --> 00:59:31.633
the hooded bandits
and crush your toy rebellion.

699
00:59:31.734 --> 00:59:33.768
I've no rebellion.

700
00:59:33.869 --> 00:59:35.637
Just a need to see you die.

701
01:00:28.675 --> 01:00:31.277
How is he?
Will he heal?

702
01:00:31.378 --> 01:00:35.114
Only blood runs.
no other humors.

703
01:00:35.215 --> 01:00:37.149
He will sleep.

704
01:00:45.157 --> 01:00:47.292
Ventris was right.

705
01:00:47.393 --> 01:00:48.826
The king's army

706
01:00:48.928 --> 01:00:52.797
will come. hunt down
the hooded thieves.

707
01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:56.167
Yea. No rock unturned until our shit
holes are split on the cradle.

708
01:00:56.269 --> 01:00:57.202
Mm.

709
01:00:59.037 --> 01:01:01.471
Your. uh...

710
01:01:01.573 --> 01:01:04.508
your dark friend--
is he. um...

711
01:01:04.609 --> 01:01:06.210
in our pope's grace?

712
01:01:06.311 --> 01:01:09.179
A moor. converted
in his homeland.

713
01:01:11.349 --> 01:01:13.483
A good Catholic like us all.

714
01:01:14.719 --> 01:01:17.721
Yea. Bloody work
is the Lord's.

715
01:01:17.822 --> 01:01:19.055
Indeed.

716
01:01:21.959 --> 01:01:24.093
I need a name
to offer my thanks.

717
01:01:24.194 --> 01:01:25.761
Gruffudd.

718
01:01:25.862 --> 01:01:28.631
You're the one
they call "the wolf."

719
01:01:28.732 --> 01:01:30.599
I'm called many
hard things.

720
01:01:30.700 --> 01:01:32.035
Most by my wife.

721
01:01:32.136 --> 01:01:34.670
Thank you for answering
our plea. Gruffudd.

722
01:01:34.771 --> 01:01:36.339
We serve each
other. friend.

723
01:01:36.440 --> 01:01:38.807
The baron's forged weapons
will be a welcome change

724
01:01:38.909 --> 01:01:40.876
from our sticks
and cobbled blades.

725
01:01:40.977 --> 01:01:42.745
Ventris has lost
nearly two legions.

726
01:01:42.846 --> 01:01:44.080
His army is weakened.

727
01:01:44.181 --> 01:01:45.814
We're not ready to storm walls.

728
01:01:45.916 --> 01:01:47.417
Even with noble swords.

729
01:01:47.518 --> 01:01:51.353
But word of this victory
will spread and it will inspire.

730
01:01:51.454 --> 01:01:52.687
Our numbers
will grow.

731
01:01:52.788 --> 01:01:54.423
I have no doubt.

732
01:01:54.524 --> 01:01:57.692
Godspeed for your knight's
return to sound body.

733
01:01:57.793 --> 01:01:59.994
An unlikely ally
in our fight.

734
01:02:00.096 --> 01:02:01.996
Let him know there
may come a time

735
01:02:02.098 --> 01:02:03.798
when I collect
on this favor.

736
01:02:13.008 --> 01:02:15.109
Toran. Moor!

737
01:02:21.083 --> 01:02:22.650
You crazy witch!

738
01:02:29.357 --> 01:02:30.758
To what end

739
01:02:30.859 --> 01:02:32.794
does this devilry serve?

740
01:02:47.041 --> 01:02:49.009
The baron has returned?

741
01:02:49.110 --> 01:02:52.012
No. But I have
news of his need.

742
01:02:52.113 --> 01:02:54.214
At Heaven's Eye.
we saw the rebel symbols.

743
01:02:54.315 --> 01:02:57.584
Lord Ventris sent me back
to secure more troops.

744
01:02:59.419 --> 01:03:01.887
Sent you back? Alone?

745
01:03:01.989 --> 01:03:03.656
Not to spare arms he may need.

746
01:03:03.757 --> 01:03:05.691
I welcomed the risk
of riding apart.

747
01:03:17.470 --> 01:03:20.006
Gather what men we can spare.

748
01:03:20.107 --> 01:03:21.774
With haste.

749
01:03:25.411 --> 01:03:27.279
Shall I find
the baroness?

750
01:03:27.380 --> 01:03:30.282
No. You should find a bath.

751
01:03:30.383 --> 01:03:32.951
You reek of shit.

752
01:03:33.052 --> 01:03:34.453
And fear.

753
01:04:26.004 --> 01:04:28.805
You join the living.

754
01:04:28.906 --> 01:04:30.506
Who did this?

755
01:04:30.607 --> 01:04:32.709
The healer.

756
01:04:32.810 --> 01:04:34.744
She offered no reason.

757
01:05:04.974 --> 01:05:06.975
Cut her binds.

758
01:05:20.456 --> 01:05:22.923
Why did you cut and scar me?

759
01:05:23.024 --> 01:05:25.727
To save you.

760
01:05:25.827 --> 01:05:28.162
Your only chance

761
01:05:28.263 --> 01:05:30.965
to live is to be supposed dead.

762
01:05:33.301 --> 01:05:35.335
He gives you that gift.

763
01:05:53.755 --> 01:05:56.222
Who are you. woman?

764
01:05:56.324 --> 01:05:58.057
Truly.

765
01:05:58.159 --> 01:06:01.094
What's your
interest in me?

766
01:06:03.598 --> 01:06:07.100
You have a fate...

767
01:06:07.201 --> 01:06:09.135
that you must learn to hold.

768
01:06:09.236 --> 01:06:14.107
One that will forever
mark your place in time.

769
01:06:16.143 --> 01:06:18.812
I am here to help
tell that story.

770
01:06:20.848 --> 01:06:22.883
My story is over.

771
01:06:22.984 --> 01:06:24.784
No.

772
01:06:24.886 --> 01:06:28.221
It is just begun.

773
01:06:28.322 --> 01:06:31.356
The angel spoke the truth.

774
01:06:35.395 --> 01:06:37.596
The angel?

775
01:06:37.697 --> 01:06:40.833
The bright child
who came to you.

776
01:06:42.669 --> 01:06:44.336
How...

777
01:06:46.339 --> 01:06:50.375
I've never whispered
a word of that to anyone.

778
01:06:52.412 --> 01:06:55.180
I hear the same voices.

779
01:06:58.684 --> 01:07:02.554
It's time to lay down
this sword. Wilkin Brattle.

780
01:07:04.157 --> 01:07:06.291
Your savior needs you

781
01:07:06.392 --> 01:07:09.561
to live the life
of a different man.

782
01:07:37.633 --> 01:07:39.633
Unhitch one of the
horses. brother.

783
01:07:39.734 --> 01:07:42.102
Then go join the
others at the caves.

784
01:07:42.203 --> 01:07:45.839
I think I'll finish
the ride. friend.

785
01:07:45.940 --> 01:07:48.542
A plan hatched by a witch--
what's to worry?

786
01:07:50.545 --> 01:07:55.148
We deliver the dead. tell
the tale. and ride off.

787
01:07:55.250 --> 01:07:57.817
Free men. no price
on our head.

788
01:07:57.918 --> 01:07:59.685
It's a sound devise.

789
01:07:59.787 --> 01:08:02.221
Simple enough an executioner
could carry it forth.

790
01:08:04.323 --> 01:08:06.391
And what say
of your purpose.

791
01:08:06.492 --> 01:08:10.062
What name for you?
Sneermonger?

792
01:08:12.132 --> 01:08:16.068
Well. my da. he wanted
to call me Marshal.

793
01:08:16.169 --> 01:08:18.771
But my ma thought it
too destined to war.

794
01:08:18.872 --> 01:08:21.673
Ma got the name.
da got the destiny.

795
01:08:21.775 --> 01:08:23.708
Yea. indeed.

796
01:08:23.809 --> 01:08:25.710
And what of your father?

797
01:08:25.811 --> 01:08:27.746
You never tell of anything.

798
01:08:30.449 --> 01:08:33.752
There's nothing to tell.
I don't have one.

799
01:09:18.995 --> 01:09:20.396
Pardon. Baroness.

800
01:09:21.965 --> 01:09:23.499
Outsiders have come.

801
01:09:23.600 --> 01:09:24.934
They bring sad news.

802
01:09:40.115 --> 01:09:42.116
Bring him down.

803
01:10:18.953 --> 01:10:22.089
My deepest condolences.
Lady Love.

804
01:10:22.190 --> 01:10:24.458
Let's bring you and the baron
into the castle

805
01:10:24.559 --> 01:10:26.493
so you can mourn in peace.

806
01:10:37.070 --> 01:10:40.407
Have the baron taken
to the sacrament room.

807
01:10:50.817 --> 01:10:53.151
Who are you?

808
01:10:56.155 --> 01:10:58.156
Gawain Maddox. milady.

809
01:10:58.257 --> 01:11:02.193
Punisher by trade.
from the southern land.

810
01:11:02.295 --> 01:11:04.195
This is Marshal.

811
01:11:04.297 --> 01:11:08.999
a journey soldier-- he aids me
in the capture of the accused.

812
01:11:09.100 --> 01:11:11.436
Tell me of his death.

813
01:11:11.537 --> 01:11:14.605
We met the baron
at Heaven's Eye.

814
01:11:14.706 --> 01:11:16.607
Called upon us
to ride with him.

815
01:11:16.708 --> 01:11:18.208
At the grass fields.

816
01:11:18.310 --> 01:11:20.445
they crossed a band
of hooded thieves.

817
01:11:20.546 --> 01:11:21.879
Took a fierce run.

818
01:11:21.980 --> 01:11:24.515
Noblemen cut down
the seven of them.

819
01:11:24.616 --> 01:11:26.683
Before the baron could rally.

820
01:11:26.784 --> 01:11:28.585
rebels attacked.

821
01:11:28.686 --> 01:11:30.921
50 or more.

822
01:11:31.021 --> 01:11:34.558
Caught the ranks tired
and out of formation.

823
01:11:34.659 --> 01:11:38.595
Your husband fought gallantly.
but the numbers were too steep.

824
01:11:39.997 --> 01:11:41.631
I'm sorry.

825
01:11:45.769 --> 01:11:47.603
Old men and boys.

826
01:11:47.704 --> 01:11:49.972
Your mail-clad soldiers
were too heavy to carry.

827
01:11:52.041 --> 01:11:54.743
We can send troops there
to collect the others.

828
01:11:54.845 --> 01:11:57.746
And what brings
an executioner to Ventrishire?

829
01:11:57.848 --> 01:11:59.648
Work. milady.

830
01:11:59.749 --> 01:12:01.684
I travel. go where
my services are needed.

831
01:12:01.785 --> 01:12:03.719
He lies!

832
01:12:05.821 --> 01:12:07.589
This man is
not the executioner.

833
01:12:09.692 --> 01:12:11.526
He's one of the thieves.

834
01:12:11.627 --> 01:12:13.060
As is that one.

835
01:12:13.161 --> 01:12:15.997
You're the liar. sir.

836
01:12:16.098 --> 01:12:19.233
I've traveled with Gawain
for many years.

837
01:12:19.334 --> 01:12:21.803
Dispatch a messenger
to Glamorgan for proof.

838
01:12:21.904 --> 01:12:24.705
There is no other face
looks like this one.

839
01:12:24.806 --> 01:12:26.907
We just came

840
01:12:27.008 --> 01:12:28.876
to deliver the dead.

841
01:12:28.977 --> 01:12:30.911
Out of respect.

842
01:12:31.012 --> 01:12:32.880
We'll leave if it upsets
your court.

843
01:12:32.981 --> 01:12:36.383
You'll stay and be quartered.

844
01:12:36.484 --> 01:12:39.720
The remedy for this dispute
is already here.

845
01:12:41.222 --> 01:12:43.356
The wife and children
of Maddox. sent here

846
01:12:43.457 --> 01:12:45.591
to wait for his return.

847
01:12:49.163 --> 01:12:51.498
Come forward.

848
01:12:54.402 --> 01:12:56.802
Tell us the truth.

849
01:12:56.904 --> 01:12:59.239
Is this man indeed your husband?

850
01:13:28.733 --> 01:13:30.668
I'm sorry.

851
01:13:37.376 --> 01:13:39.377
My love.

852
01:13:41.913 --> 01:13:45.082
Good Maddy. thank God
you've come back safe.

853
01:13:49.854 --> 01:13:51.655
This is lunacy!

854
01:13:51.756 --> 01:13:54.224
She conspires with him!

855
01:13:58.463 --> 01:14:01.330
Such tragedy...

856
01:14:01.431 --> 01:14:03.800
lands on my name this day.

857
01:14:09.640 --> 01:14:11.173
My dearest friend.

858
01:14:11.274 --> 01:14:14.611
a life snuffed...

859
01:14:14.712 --> 01:14:17.146
not in a fitting battle...

860
01:14:18.415 --> 01:14:21.617
but by the ambush
of painted dogs.

861
01:14:24.120 --> 01:14:27.489
And my kin.

862
01:14:27.590 --> 01:14:30.391
Caught between two tales.

863
01:14:30.493 --> 01:14:32.293
I speak only truth.
dear brother.

864
01:14:32.394 --> 01:14:34.963
I have nothing to gain
from such a lie.

865
01:14:35.064 --> 01:14:37.165
These men are
the bandits we pursued.

866
01:14:37.266 --> 01:14:39.167
Did battle in the
fields beyond the eye.

867
01:14:39.268 --> 01:14:42.170
I myself
and other honored knights

868
01:14:42.271 --> 01:14:44.272
heard you tell
how you were dispatched

869
01:14:44.373 --> 01:14:46.841
<i>before</i> any such fray.

870
01:14:50.646 --> 01:14:52.113
Yea.

871
01:14:52.214 --> 01:14:54.482
- I did. but...
- You may have

872
01:14:54.583 --> 01:14:58.101
nothing to gain. but
you've much to hide.

873
01:14:58.186 --> 01:15:01.756
We saw this man at the fray.

874
01:15:01.857 --> 01:15:04.759
He tucked tail and slithered
away. letting his brothers

875
01:15:04.860 --> 01:15:07.047
fall to the curs.

876
01:15:07.596 --> 01:15:09.731
That's why he lies.

877
01:15:09.832 --> 01:15:11.233
'Cause we know
the truth.

878
01:15:11.334 --> 01:15:12.667
That's...

879
01:15:12.768 --> 01:15:14.702
- I tell you. these are the...
- Enough!

880
01:15:26.248 --> 01:15:28.916
So. then. Reeve...

881
01:15:29.017 --> 01:15:32.219
you are either a false accuser

882
01:15:32.320 --> 01:15:34.621
or you deserted your commander
in battle!

883
01:15:36.623 --> 01:15:39.492
Both come with
a punishment of death!

884
01:15:41.628 --> 01:15:44.097
Please...

885
01:15:44.198 --> 01:15:45.999
Milus...

886
01:15:46.100 --> 01:15:47.566
brother...

887
01:15:47.667 --> 01:15:49.102
do not do this.

888
01:15:49.703 --> 01:15:51.169
Take him!

889
01:15:51.271 --> 01:15:52.838
Brother. we are blood.

890
01:15:52.939 --> 01:15:54.572
Do not betray me.
Damn you!

891
01:15:54.673 --> 01:15:56.073
Damn your half-hatred!

892
01:15:56.174 --> 01:15:57.241
Damn y...

893
01:16:01.980 --> 01:16:04.616
I'm gonna speak
to the King!

894
01:16:04.717 --> 01:16:05.983
Curse you!

895
01:16:06.084 --> 01:16:07.519
I'll curse you
from hell!

896
01:16:17.495 --> 01:16:20.898
My shame is only
outdone by my sadness.

897
01:16:22.934 --> 01:16:26.202
My deepest sympathies. Baroness.

898
01:16:26.304 --> 01:16:29.673
I am in your service.
whatever the need.

899
01:16:31.275 --> 01:16:33.409
Thank you. Milus.

900
01:16:35.479 --> 01:16:38.380
I will do haste
with manor law and trial.

901
01:16:40.484 --> 01:16:42.184
It is fitting...

902
01:16:42.285 --> 01:16:44.286
that the man falsely accused

903
01:16:44.387 --> 01:16:47.924
be the one who is skilled
to take his head.

904
01:16:59.335 --> 01:17:02.771
Welcome to Castle Ventris.
executioner.

905
01:17:34.068 --> 01:17:36.302
Baroness.

906
01:17:36.403 --> 01:17:39.138
The priest. he said I could
come for evening prayer.

907
01:17:39.239 --> 01:17:40.740
Please. sit.

908
01:17:40.841 --> 01:17:42.809
I welcome the chapel's use.

909
01:17:42.910 --> 01:17:45.712
Few spend time here but me.

910
01:17:49.450 --> 01:17:51.451
Do you mind?

911
01:17:53.353 --> 01:17:54.987
Please.

912
01:18:04.030 --> 01:18:06.031
I wouldn't think

913
01:18:06.133 --> 01:18:09.569
one of your trade would
complicate things with prayer.

914
01:18:12.106 --> 01:18:15.408
Perhaps it takes you
in deeper.

915
01:18:20.347 --> 01:18:23.248
May I ask how
this happened?

916
01:18:25.418 --> 01:18:27.719
It was given to me
by a healer.

917
01:18:27.820 --> 01:18:30.888
A holy woman.

918
01:18:30.990 --> 01:18:33.291
A reminder
of my need for faith.

919
01:18:35.794 --> 01:18:37.895
Your soldier gave
the impression

920
01:18:37.997 --> 01:18:39.831
it distinguished
you for some time.

921
01:18:39.932 --> 01:18:43.401
Yet. the burn looks fresh.

922
01:18:43.503 --> 01:18:46.171
I renew the vow
when my faith wavers.

923
01:18:50.175 --> 01:18:52.576
You're bleeding.

924
01:18:52.678 --> 01:18:54.979
Yea.

925
01:18:55.080 --> 01:18:58.415
An angry branch
on last night's ride.

926
01:18:58.517 --> 01:19:00.885
May I?

927
01:19:00.986 --> 01:19:03.287
In here. milady?

928
01:19:03.388 --> 01:19:04.922
No better one

929
01:19:05.024 --> 01:19:07.324
to heal you than Him.

930
01:19:18.202 --> 01:19:20.570
The physicker
should look at this.

931
01:19:40.224 --> 01:19:42.625
I'll find the physicker.

932
01:19:42.726 --> 01:19:46.028
No. Stay.

933
01:19:46.129 --> 01:19:47.830
Finish your devotion.

934
01:19:47.931 --> 01:19:50.933
I'll have him find you.

935
01:20:17.293 --> 01:20:20.962
Baroness?

936
01:20:21.063 --> 01:20:24.165
I sent an emissary
to London

937
01:20:24.267 --> 01:20:29.137
and one to Erik's brother
in Coventry.

938
01:20:29.239 --> 01:20:34.174
I'm sure our king will offer
comfort and guidance

939
01:20:34.276 --> 01:20:36.777
of how we proceed
to govern.

940
01:20:36.878 --> 01:20:39.947
We proceed by
burying my husband.

941
01:20:41.182 --> 01:20:43.484
Yes.

942
01:20:43.585 --> 01:20:45.686
Of course.

943
01:20:47.856 --> 01:20:50.258
Another thought.

944
01:20:50.359 --> 01:20:52.292
my lady.

945
01:20:52.393 --> 01:20:55.662
This executioner--

946
01:20:55.764 --> 01:20:57.631
his arrival.

947
01:20:57.732 --> 01:21:01.168
although it brought sadness--

948
01:21:01.269 --> 01:21:03.470
it could turn
to good fortune.

949
01:21:03.571 --> 01:21:04.905
How so?

950
01:21:05.006 --> 01:21:07.474
If we secure him
and his soldier.

951
01:21:07.575 --> 01:21:10.477
we gain skilled men
to hunt offenders

952
01:21:10.578 --> 01:21:12.813
and carry out the correction.

953
01:21:12.914 --> 01:21:17.350
Sends a sound message.

954
01:21:17.451 --> 01:21:20.754
Ventrishire will not
suffer lawlessness.

955
01:21:23.624 --> 01:21:27.093
That's well advised.
dear Chamberlain.

956
01:21:27.194 --> 01:21:30.062
Good. I'll draft the letters

957
01:21:30.164 --> 01:21:32.465
that bind them.

958
01:21:51.618 --> 01:21:55.587
I have news. Maddox.

959
01:21:57.190 --> 01:22:01.293
The trial was swift.
the guilt clear.

960
01:22:02.862 --> 01:22:05.297
We will stage the execution
in the village square

961
01:22:05.398 --> 01:22:07.700
midday tomorrow.

962
01:22:13.873 --> 01:22:16.541
He's your blood.

963
01:22:16.642 --> 01:22:18.977
There must be some...

964
01:22:19.078 --> 01:22:22.347
due leniency. a brother's mercy?

965
01:22:22.448 --> 01:22:24.716
You rid me of a mistake

966
01:22:24.817 --> 01:22:29.221
influenced by familial guilt.

967
01:22:30.890 --> 01:22:34.659
No kin. no worries.

968
01:22:36.528 --> 01:22:39.263
But of course.
you wouldn't understand that.

969
01:22:39.364 --> 01:22:42.933
Being a family man.

970
01:22:43.034 --> 01:22:46.036
And you're the final word
of justice here?

971
01:22:48.239 --> 01:22:51.542
As well as chancellor
and advisor.

972
01:22:51.643 --> 01:22:55.279
You'll find that nothing passes

973
01:22:55.380 --> 01:22:58.716
through this shire
without me touching it.

974
01:22:58.817 --> 01:23:01.151
I'm afraid that's a lesson
I'll have to miss.

975
01:23:01.252 --> 01:23:03.153
I move on after tomorrow.

976
01:23:03.254 --> 01:23:05.322
Ah. but that's my news.

977
01:23:05.423 --> 01:23:09.593
You and your soldier
will stay on.

978
01:23:09.694 --> 01:23:12.162
Your position is now standing.

979
01:23:16.734 --> 01:23:19.136
We're journeyman.

980
01:23:19.237 --> 01:23:21.004
Travelers.

981
01:23:21.106 --> 01:23:22.805
Now. you have a home.

982
01:23:22.906 --> 01:23:26.842
I'm sure that will be
a comfort to your

983
01:23:26.943 --> 01:23:29.912
wife and wee things.

984
01:23:43.793 --> 01:23:46.228
Why are you doing this?

985
01:23:48.897 --> 01:23:51.733
Our buried truths bind us.

986
01:23:51.834 --> 01:23:54.736
And your skills
will serve me.

987
01:24:00.943 --> 01:24:03.345
I need a man

988
01:24:03.446 --> 01:24:05.747
with the heart
of a dragon.

989
01:24:39.547 --> 01:24:41.982
Ludwig?

990
01:25:09.543 --> 01:25:13.246
We need to ready our faith.

991
01:25:13.347 --> 01:25:18.117
<i>Ja. meine Liebe.</i>

992
01:25:43.732 --> 01:25:46.167
<i>Ego auctoritate</i>

993
01:25:46.268 --> 01:25:49.337
<i>ipsius te absolvo</i>

994
01:25:49.438 --> 01:25:53.707
<i>ab omni vinculo excommunicationis
et interdicti...</i>

995
01:25:53.808 --> 01:25:56.777
<i>...in quantum possum</i>

996
01:25:56.877 --> 01:25:59.713
<i>et tu indiges.</i>

997
01:25:59.814 --> 01:26:02.949
<i>Ego te absolvo</i>

998
01:26:03.050 --> 01:26:06.019
<i>a peccatis tuis</i>

999
01:26:06.120 --> 01:26:08.822
<i>in nomine Patris.</i>
<i>et Filii.</i>

1000
01:26:08.923 --> 01:26:10.589
<i>et Spiritus Sancti. Amen.</i>

1001
01:26:32.911 --> 01:26:35.279
Blades have been grinded. sir.

1002
01:27:28.431 --> 01:27:30.765
Help me.

1003
01:28:17.845 --> 01:28:21.481
Always.

1004
01:28:35.996 --> 01:28:37.429
You'll need this. headsman.

1005
01:28:37.530 --> 01:28:40.299
Little Rand
was full of shit.

1006
01:28:42.302 --> 01:28:44.470
A stuffed clown.

1007
01:28:45.806 --> 01:28:47.207
You best take another.

1008
01:28:47.308 --> 01:28:49.075
Yeah. His ass will spout
like a fountain.

1009
01:28:51.845 --> 01:28:53.279
Who did you spring from?

1010
01:29:31.184 --> 01:29:34.500
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

1010
01:29:35.305 --> 01:30:35.789
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
